OL,3,CWhy is an independent regulator being
OL,4,Cestablished in English football?
OL,6,FThe Football Association (FA),
OL,7,Fmeanwhile, welcomed the commitment to
OL,8,Fstrengthen independent financial
OL,9,Fregulation within the sport, while the
OL,10,FFootball Supporters' Association (FSA)
OL,11,Fcommented that it "provides a means to
OL,12,Fintervene and stop clubs being run
OL,13,Finto the ground, protect the heritage
OL,14,Fof clubs, give supporters a much
OL,15,Fbigger voice in the running of the
OL,16,Fgame and prevent any chance of
OL,17,Fdomestic clubs joining a breakaway
OL,18,FEuropean Super League".
